Morphology of the Diagram
Main Process Flow

Student completes homework.
– The student finishes the assigned work.

Student uploads assignment.
– The student submits the assignment through the system.

System notifies instructor.
– The system sends a notification to the instructor.

Instructor uploads feedback and grade.
– The instructor reviews the assignment and provides both feedback and a grade.

Student views feedback and updates learning.
– The student checks the feedback and adjusts their learning accordingly.

Rework (Possible Outcome).
– If necessary, the student revises or reworks the assignment.

Branches / Identified Issues

Delay (Red Triangle)
– A delay may occur in the instructor’s grading or feedback process.

Confusion (Yellow Triangle)
– The student may misunderstand the feedback, causing confusion.

Rework (Blue Triangle)
– The student may need to redo or update their assignment based on feedback.
